1
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:34,900
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:37,810
[Episode 26]

3
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,950
Nini, don't be upset, okay?

4
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:48,509
Do you see that uncle in there

5
00:01:48,509 --> 00:01:50,350
who's watering the flowers?

6
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,120
He knows magic.

7
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,310
He's very powerful.

8
00:01:53,310 --> 00:01:54,509
Go talk to him in a bit.

9
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,430
Just say, "Uncle,

10
00:01:55,430 --> 00:01:56,710
my magic wand is broken.

11
00:01:56,710 --> 00:01:58,440
Could you find me another one?"

12
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,980
Who's this kid?

13
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:04,920
Go play with those flowers for a while.

14
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:06,150
See if there's any

15
00:02:06,190 --> 00:02:07,790
other amazing magic in there.

16
00:02:07,790 --> 00:02:09,430
I'll have a word with Mr. Magic here,

17
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:11,430
and I'll come find you in a bit, okay?

18
00:02:11,750 --> 00:02:12,280
Go ahead.

19
00:02:13,150 --> 00:02:14,210
Look at that blue flower—

20
00:02:14,210 --> 00:02:16,000
it's almost the same color
as your clothes.

21
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,430
She's the kid from Bed 15.

22
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,490
Her name is Nini.

23
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,880
They say she has delusional disorder.

24
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:22,400
You see that wooden stick

25
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,630
she's holding in her hand?

26
00:02:23,630 --> 00:02:25,470
According to her, it's a magic wand.

27
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:27,730
But that stick got snapped a few days ago,

28
00:02:28,130 --> 00:02:30,150
and she said that
with the magic wand gone,

29
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,870
the whole world had turned gray.

30
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:33,530
She's been crying ever since.

31
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,870
Just snap off another one for her then.

32
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:35,710
It's just a tree branch, isn't it?

33
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:36,560
Take a look.

34
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,750
I couldn't find one that looks the same.

35
00:02:38,750 --> 00:02:39,400
Let me see.

36
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:42,750
Talk to her nicely.
Don't let her start crying again.

37
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:44,400
Gosh, so am I supposed to
talk to her or not?

38
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,800
Sure, but in a gentle way.

39
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:51,560
Nini, come on, show it to Mr. Magic.

40
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,430
Nini.

41
00:02:53,470 --> 00:02:55,200
What kind of magic wand is this?

42
00:02:56,970 --> 00:02:57,490
This...

43
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,360
What can this magic wand do?

44
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:03,710
It can conjure up all sorts of things.

45
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,400
It can conjure up things, huh?

46
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,240
It's just a peach tree branch, though.

47
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:09,700
It's okay. I'll go snap off
a few more for you.

48
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:12,870
I-It has to be exactly the same,

49
00:03:12,870 --> 00:03:14,400
only then can the spell work

50
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:17,680
and bring color back to the world.

51
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:24,880
Chunchun.

52
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:26,750
Look.

53
00:03:28,110 --> 00:03:29,829
A gold branch,

54
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:31,560
and a silver branch.

55
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,910
Which one is yours?

56
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:35,150
I choose...

57
00:03:36,030 --> 00:03:36,710
This one.

58
00:03:38,310 --> 00:03:40,030
This is the original one, right?

59
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:41,310
-It snapped.
-The wooden branch.

60
00:03:41,310 --> 00:03:42,310
Yeah, it snapped.

61
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:44,240
But this one I found is already

62
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,310
the closest match.

63
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:46,840
It does look quite similar.

64
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,860
Even the bend is the same.

65
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:48,510
Right?

66
00:03:49,310 --> 00:03:50,400
You'll just have to tell her that

67
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:53,060
the branch went back to the forest
and grew a bit.

68
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:55,170
Alright. Mission accomplished.

69
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,600
There was a branch on this piece of wood

70
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,440
which is round and straight.

71
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,560
I sawed it off.

72
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:05,520
You can keep it as a charm.

73
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:09,070
It can protect you and ward off evil.

74
00:04:10,610 --> 00:04:11,290
Driver!

75
00:04:11,430 --> 00:04:11,870
Wait!

76
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:14,840
Driver!

77
00:04:17,019 --> 00:04:18,620
We were just a few steps away.

78
00:04:21,190 --> 00:04:22,560
Didn't the driver see us just now?

79
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,310
Probably not.

80
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:24,480
Let's go rest in the pavilion

81
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,120
and wait for the next one.

82
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:27,120
So he didn't realize that
I wanted to catch that bus, huh?

83
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:30,050
He probably thought
you were just taking a walk here.

84
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:36,140
Back in school,

85
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,600
Xia Lei told me that

86
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:40,560
a bus stop

87
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:45,470
is sometimes like a microcosm of life.

88
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,630
Some people

89
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,680
wait at the bus stop,

90
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,140
but end up getting picked up
by a private car;

91
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,720
some people

92
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,680
just get on the bus and leave;

93
00:04:57,510 --> 00:04:58,830
while some people

94
00:04:59,310 --> 00:05:01,430
even miss the bus in the end.

95
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:04,310
I just listened and let it pass back then.

96
00:05:04,310 --> 00:05:05,630
I didn't take it seriously.

97
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:07,720
I haven't realized until recent years

98
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:10,180
that I'm one of those people
who miss the bus.

99
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:18,800
It's not like there's only one bus.

100
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:22,120
If you miss this one, just catch the next.

101
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:23,950
There will always be another.

102
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,190
But don't you feel anxious?

103
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:26,000
I don't.

104
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,480
Maybe you feel anxious

105
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:34,360
because you're the only one waiting.

106
00:05:39,450 --> 00:05:40,050
Is that so?

107
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:43,720
Maybe.

108
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:46,750
Keep this for now.

109
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:52,210
It looks quite nice with the red string.

110
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:56,120
Burn this part when you get back.

111
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:15,120
This is my first time here at night.

112
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,100
It's so beautiful.

113
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:19,730
Have you been here before?

114
00:06:20,070 --> 00:06:24,190
Didn't you say that the glass has to break

115
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:26,920
for more sunlight to come in?

116
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:31,700
I didn't expect the moonlight at night
to look this beautiful too.

117
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:33,800
You know what?

118
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,390
Actually, today,

119
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:40,240
I'm really, really happy.

120
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,120
Me too.

121
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,720
Why are you happy?

122
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,630
Because

123
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:50,190
we helped Nini get her magic wand back.

124
00:06:51,190 --> 00:06:54,120
Actually, this is what it was like
back in our plant.

125
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,170
No matter who it was,

126
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,190
everyone looked out for each other.

127
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,950
That familiar feeling is back.

128
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,800
Don't you want to get out of here?

129
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:10,360
Do you think I'd fit in out there?

130
00:07:14,130 --> 00:07:14,990
Zhang Xiaoman.

131
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,080
Let me ask you something.

132
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:23,590
Have you really let it go?

133
00:07:26,410 --> 00:07:27,440
I've accept it.

134
00:07:31,430 --> 00:07:32,960
Actually, all these years,

135
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:38,190
I've been trying to catch up to Xiaodan.

136
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,050
I thought I could definitely catch up,

137
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:47,670
even if it had to take a while.

138
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,240
But later, I realized

139
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,409
that sometimes,

140
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,240
a gap is just a gap—

141
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:01,760
it's not something effort alone can close.

142
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:05,720
I kept chasing,

143
00:08:07,530 --> 00:08:09,030
giving it my all.

144
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:11,510
Even when I was exhausted,

145
00:08:11,510 --> 00:08:13,950
I kept running forward.

146
00:08:16,310 --> 00:08:17,070
In the end,

147
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,710
didn't I just run myself into the sea?

148
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:23,870
So how do you feel?

149
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,450
Unwilling to let go?

150
00:08:27,580 --> 00:08:28,260
No.

151
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,049
I don't feel unwilling.

152
00:08:33,210 --> 00:08:35,730
I've got no regrets, either.

153
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,929
Because in this relationship,

154
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:38,720
I...

155
00:08:40,789 --> 00:08:41,919
I really did my best.

156
00:08:42,909 --> 00:08:43,840
And I

157
00:08:45,790 --> 00:08:47,080
truly gave it my all.

158
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:50,670
If this is how it ends,

159
00:08:53,790 --> 00:08:54,720
then I accept it.

160
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:00,080
As long as you don't regret it.
That's what matters.

161
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:00,940
Actually, I...

162
00:09:02,510 --> 00:09:03,720
I've always wanted

163
00:09:08,110 --> 00:09:10,000
to thank you.

164
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,360
During this time we've spent together,

165
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:19,050
you've actually been
a kind of companionship for me.

166
00:09:20,790 --> 00:09:22,120
This companionship...

167
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:26,550
Has been a form of healing,
even a kind of redemption.

168
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:33,000
I-I'm truly, truly happy

169
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,720
to have had this time with you.

170
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,320
And I also want to thank you

171
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:40,960
for helping me emerge from

172
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:43,110
such a chaotic state,

173
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,320
allowing me

174
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,600
to face the world once again.

175
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:56,510
I want to thank you too.

176
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:00,050
What I said to you on that rainy day—

177
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:02,770
I've never shared them

178
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:05,750
with anyone else in my life.

179
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,270
You're the first—

180
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,060
and probably the only one.

181
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,840
Being with you,

182
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,910
I realized that

183
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,390
putting down those burdens

184
00:10:28,390 --> 00:10:29,990
actually feels pretty good.

185
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:34,940
Zhang Xiaoman.

186
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:39,550
You're the sweetness in my life.

187
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:43,300
Thank you.

188
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:46,910
The wind stops at the autumn waters.

189
00:10:54,490 --> 00:10:55,300
Alright.

190
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,240
Let's go out together,

191
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:06,290
take a fresh look at this world,

192
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:07,550
and face life.

193
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,720
You've made up your mind?

194
00:11:14,030 --> 00:11:15,290
Let's go out together.

195
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:16,960
Then...

196
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,220
Zhang Xiaoman.

197
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,040
Welcome home.

198
00:11:52,810 --> 00:12:02,980
[Tiecheng Anning Hospital]

199
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:05,840
What's wrong? Not in a hurry
to catch the bus this time?

200
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,770
Want to run a bit?

201
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:10,010
Well, since we're both here,
what's the rush?

202
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:18,020
Have you decided yet?

203
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:21,520
Now that you're out of the hospital,
what do you plan to do?

204
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:23,470
Haven't really thought about it.

205
00:12:23,470 --> 00:12:25,550
No matter what, I'll just come out first

206
00:12:25,550 --> 00:12:27,150
and get prepared.

207
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,740
Then I can do anything.

208
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,030
I can help you out with your flower shop
for now.

209
00:12:32,030 --> 00:12:33,860
Sure. You're welcome anytime.

210
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,060
Zhang Xiaoman,

211
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:46,080
I'm telling you seriously.

212
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,670
In our life together in the future,

213
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:50,700
we might encounter some difficulties,

214
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:51,890
and there might be

215
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,780
some messy things happening.

216
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,160
Don't say that.

217
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:58,240
You said it yourself that
it's our life together.

218
00:12:58,550 --> 00:13:00,840
So I must take the initiative
to take on this responsibility,

219
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:01,480
right?

220
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:04,000
No matter what happens in the future,
I'll carry it all.

221
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,440
Don't worry. I won't fall.

222
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,510
I'll carry it with you.

223
00:13:06,510 --> 00:13:07,600
I won't let you fall.

224
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:08,240
Neither of us will fall.

225
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,100
Yeah, neither.

226
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,240
I promise you.

227
00:13:17,830 --> 00:13:18,860
From now on,

228
00:13:18,890 --> 00:13:22,750
whether we take the bus or walk,

229
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:26,220
I'll hold your hand tight

230
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:27,930
and never let go.

231
00:13:28,090 --> 00:13:30,020
I'll go hand in hand with you, okay?

232
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:36,840
In the future...

233
00:13:38,790 --> 00:13:39,790
We'll take a taxi.

234
00:13:44,790 --> 00:13:46,960
We're home. We're home.

235
00:13:51,870 --> 00:13:52,720
Xiaoman?

236
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,630
You're out of the hospital?

237
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:55,960
You should have told me!

238
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:57,760
Did you miss me?

239
00:13:57,790 --> 00:13:58,390
Of course.

240
00:13:58,550 --> 00:14:00,480
I could've picked you up in the taxi
if you'd asked.

241
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,550
Taking the bus was fine.

242
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:03,480
You should hurry and pick up fares.

243
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:07,730
You two are in love?

244
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:09,960
D-Don't...
Don't talk like that in front of her.

245
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,090
Hi, Sister-in-law.

246
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,200
How come I didn't notice it
back at the dance hall?

247
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,910
Notice it? If you had noticed it earlier,
things would've been a mess.

248
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:16,230
I support you two being together.

249
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,890
It's definitely a good thing!

250
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:18,960
W-What's wrong with you?

251
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:21,560
Are you drunk or what
this early in the morning?

252
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:22,670
No, not at all. I was about to
start my shift.

253
00:14:22,670 --> 00:14:24,960
Then why are you...
Talking all that nonsense?

254
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:26,160
It's okay. It's okay.

255
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,260
See? Chunchun is way more easygoing.

256
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:29,320
Just go.

257
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,150
Go on ahead.

258
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:31,640
Alright then... Let's catch up tonight.

259
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,100
Sure. Let's talk tonight.

260
00:14:35,670 --> 00:14:36,670
Come on, Xiaoman.

261
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:38,320
Have some sunflower seeds.

262
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:41,270
Xiaoman, what are your plans
for the future?

263
00:14:41,270 --> 00:14:42,520
Haven't really thought about it.

264
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:45,000
Anyway, since Chunchun's running
a flower shop right now,

265
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:47,030
I'll help out there for a bit.

266
00:14:48,910 --> 00:14:49,630
Chunchun?

267
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,270
Is she the one who grew flowers with you?

268
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:55,600
Yeah, right. That girl.

269
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:57,550
She's nice.

270
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,780
She doesn't seem pretentious at all.

271
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,630
Which girl are you talking about?

272
00:15:02,630 --> 00:15:03,510
Who's nice?

273
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,320
Do I know her?

274
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:07,270
Just do your work. Always getting fired up
the moment you hear "girl."

275
00:15:07,270 --> 00:15:09,630
Where's your wife?
Why didn't you bring her along?

276
00:15:09,630 --> 00:15:12,160
The kid's too young.
Someone has to stay at home.

277
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:12,920
You have no idea.

278
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,630
Watching kids is way more tiring
than working.

279
00:15:14,630 --> 00:15:15,870
Then why aren't you home watching the kid,

280
00:15:15,870 --> 00:15:16,790
but wandering around out here
all day instead?

281
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,790
Do I look like the type to watch kids?

282
00:15:19,390 --> 00:15:20,440
After we got laid off,

283
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:21,770
Factory No. 3 took me in.

284
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:23,270
But I barely worked there
for a couple of years

285
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:24,930
before they shut down as well.

286
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:26,790
My father-in-law
has passed his craft down to me.

287
00:15:26,790 --> 00:15:27,970
Now I make a living popping popcorn.

288
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,170
I'm a true craftsman.

289
00:15:29,390 --> 00:15:31,600
The point is, if I don't see
this old man here for a day,

290
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:32,320
I miss him.

291
00:15:32,360 --> 00:15:33,960
Enough, enough. Stop babbling.

292
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,490
It's giving me goosebumps.

293
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:37,120
Wipe that table clean.

294
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,030
I-It's all smeared over there.

295
00:15:38,030 --> 00:15:39,960
Our business covers dining, entertainment,
and more.

296
00:15:39,960 --> 00:15:42,790
In the future, we will also enter
the real estate industry.

297
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:43,840
Beitie Charm

298
00:15:43,870 --> 00:15:47,120
will wholeheartedly provide
the finest services

299
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,850
for the people of our hometown.

300
00:15:50,870 --> 00:15:51,280
[Beitie Charm Industrial Co., Ltd.]

301
00:15:51,430 --> 00:15:52,520
I know this guy.

302
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,600
Yeah, it's Mr. Yu.

303
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,440
Everyone knows him.

304
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,790
He's been back for 2 years—

305
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:58,240
running entertainment clubs,

306
00:15:58,240 --> 00:15:59,390
boutique malls,

307
00:15:59,390 --> 00:16:00,550
and a bunch of other businesses.

308
00:16:00,550 --> 00:16:01,680
Yeah, he's gone big.

309
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:05,440
Your major is...

310
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,090
Architectural design, right?

311
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,650
So how are your designs?

312
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:15,560
Our daughter's designs
have won awards, okay?

313
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:18,490
Are the houses you design
meant for people to live in?

314
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:21,120
Why do you have to be so mean?

315
00:16:21,550 --> 00:16:23,240
Take fashion design.

316
00:16:23,790 --> 00:16:25,390
Sometimes the clothes they design

317
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:27,750
are just meant for models on the runway.

318
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,080
They're for shows.

319
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:31,190
You can't wear them in real life.

320
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:33,150
But our daughter helped Wang Dongdong
and his wife

321
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,280
design their house.

322
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:35,790
If it weren't for her design,

323
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:38,480
they wouldn't even have had a place
to live after getting married.

324
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,600
I'll go check out

325
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,860
our daughter's design myself sometime.

326
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:45,750
Are you two having lunch?

327
00:16:45,750 --> 00:16:46,630
Xiaodan.

328
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:48,790
-Come on in.
-Chief Engineer Yan.

329
00:16:48,790 --> 00:16:50,030
-Chief Engineer Yan, you're here.
-Come on.

330
00:16:50,030 --> 00:16:50,600
Come on in.

331
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,450
Come on in. Have a seat,
Chief Engineer Yan.

332
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:53,450
Accountant Wang.

333
00:16:53,630 --> 00:16:55,780
Look at that—I've got a new surname again.

334
00:16:55,780 --> 00:16:56,970
-It's Sun. Sun.
-Accountant Sun.

335
00:16:56,970 --> 00:16:58,150
Accountant Sun. Accountant Sun.

336
00:16:58,150 --> 00:16:58,840
Well,

337
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:00,960
my dad heard I designed this house
for you two,

338
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:01,840
so he wanted to come and take a look.

339
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:03,210
Sure. Feel free to look around.

340
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:04,000
Come take a look.

341
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:04,550
Take a look.

342
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,160
Come on.

343
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:06,220
Alright, alright.

344
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:07,790
This is a small kitchen, right?

345
00:17:07,790 --> 00:17:08,349
Yeah.

346
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:10,550
So it's an open kitchen.

347
00:17:10,790 --> 00:17:12,319
How do you handle the fumes?

348
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:15,890
-And this...
-This is the bedroom.

349
00:17:16,069 --> 00:17:17,160
-Be careful.
-Let me see.

350
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:17,819
Be careful.

351
00:17:19,069 --> 00:17:20,130
Careful. Careful.

352
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,000
There's a bedroom.

353
00:17:22,030 --> 00:17:22,829
Right.

354
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:25,720
Well, this...

355
00:17:26,109 --> 00:17:27,109
What do you think?

356
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:30,830
You think it's quite pretty, don't you?

357
00:17:30,830 --> 00:17:31,890
Yeah, it's pretty.

358
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:34,640
But you see... As a home,

359
00:17:35,270 --> 00:17:38,110
first and foremost, it has to
be comfortable to live in.

360
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:39,000
-Yeah.
-Right?

361
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,600
-Right.
-Looks come second.

362
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:44,050
If it's only pretty but not comfortable,
then it's no good.

363
00:17:44,470 --> 00:17:45,750
Just like that reactor

364
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,680
I designed at our plant.

365
00:17:48,030 --> 00:17:49,640
Everyone thought it looked great.

366
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:50,570
Yeah, very nice.

367
00:17:50,590 --> 00:17:52,080
But the technicians criticized me
every day.

368
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:53,350
Why? Because it was
all show and no substance.

369
00:17:53,350 --> 00:17:54,830
That was a failed design.

370
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,880
Get it? Such a nice house,

371
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:59,610
and you tore down the main wall.

372
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:01,310
We're in the Northeast,

373
00:18:01,790 --> 00:18:02,790
and this is a one-storey house.

374
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,030
When the dead of winter comes,

375
00:18:04,030 --> 00:18:05,830
won't the wind just come howling in?

376
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:08,110
No matter how high you turn up
the heat, it'll still be cold.

377
00:18:08,110 --> 00:18:10,200
How can you feel comfortable
living in here?

378
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:10,920
-Right?
-Yeah.

379
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:11,750
-Yeah, right.
-Look.

380
00:18:11,750 --> 00:18:13,240
As expected from Chief Engineer Yan,

381
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,270
hitting the nail on the head.

382
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:15,200
As they say,

383
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,270
"the older, the wiser."

384
00:18:16,270 --> 00:18:18,200
Chief Engineer Yan spotted it
at a glance...

385
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:19,600
This is a bedroom, right?

386
00:18:20,550 --> 00:18:21,950
You put a glass door here.

387
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:22,480
Yeah.

388
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:23,880
This is another mistake.

389
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,530
It's okay, Xiaodan.

390
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,030
When you designed this house,

391
00:18:27,030 --> 00:18:28,240
you were still a student.

392
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:30,470
We really like it.
It's spacious and bright.

393
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:31,240
It's really pretty.

394
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,680
When we g-got married in this house,
we really impressed everyone.

395
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,070
Yeah.

396
00:18:33,170 --> 00:18:34,310
My dad is right.

397
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,860
My design must have caused you two

398
00:18:35,860 --> 00:18:37,440
a lot of trouble in your daily lives.

399
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,680
No, not at all.

400
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:39,160
Wait.

401
00:18:39,340 --> 00:18:42,210
Y-You designed this?

402
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:44,960
Dad, you forgot again.

403
00:18:45,570 --> 00:18:47,030
Didn't you just say

404
00:18:47,110 --> 00:18:48,000
you wanted to come over and check out

405
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:50,030
the house I designed for them?

406
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:51,560
This is it.

407
00:18:52,030 --> 00:18:53,510
Right, right.

408
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:57,650
Only forward-thinking concepts
can lead the industry.

409
00:18:57,650 --> 00:18:59,550
If we just work on houses already built—

410
00:18:59,550 --> 00:19:01,030
tearing down walls and adding tiles—

411
00:19:01,030 --> 00:19:02,400
then what do we need designers for?

412
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:03,440
But you're taking too big a step.

413
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,240
There're a lot of real-world constraints.

414
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:07,680
The construction workers on site
just can't keep up with your idea.

415
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:09,270
Then what we need to do is
solve the real-world problems,

416
00:19:09,270 --> 00:19:11,160
not question the design itself.

417
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,820
Do you know the Tower of Babel?

418
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:16,550
Yan, you've been working
for over 2 years,

419
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,450
yet you're still building a Tower of Babel
like castles in the air.

420
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:21,370
Leaving this open is also for...

421
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:21,960
Ventilation.

422
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:22,720
Ventilation. Right.

423
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,790
-The ventilation is good.
-It's not… Not really...

424
00:19:23,790 --> 00:19:25,030
Not really a bad idea, right?

425
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:25,830
-Yes.
-Right.

426
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:32,790
Xiaoman.

427
00:19:41,870 --> 00:19:42,560
Xiaoman?

428
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:01,160
Our flower shop has been getting

429
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:03,910
a lot of housewarming orders lately.

430
00:20:04,120 --> 00:20:04,960
Ordering those flower baskets.

431
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:07,420
Do you remember Mr. Gu
from when we were kids?

432
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:08,090
I remember.

433
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:11,720
I heard from Dongdong that
he's moving too.

434
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:14,590
He asked Dongdong to help him find
a moving company.

435
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:16,830
Even though he didn't like me much
back then,

436
00:20:16,830 --> 00:20:18,160
I was thinking,

437
00:20:18,270 --> 00:20:20,670
maybe we could rent a truck
and help him out?

438
00:20:20,890 --> 00:20:22,290
Absolutely. No problem.

439
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:24,350
It's only right.

440
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:27,350
Mom, I went to see Xiaoman today.

441
00:20:27,470 --> 00:20:28,330
He wasn't home.

442
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:30,280
Is he still in the hospital?

443
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:32,150
The last main dish.

444
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:33,650
Coming right up.

445
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,840
Here. What are you two chatting about?

446
00:20:38,350 --> 00:20:39,610
I heard something about clothes?

447
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:41,240
We were talking about how sharp you look.

448
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:41,920
Really?

449
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:44,440
As long as you didn't say I look crazy.

450
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:46,350
We said you look dapper in this shirt.

451
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:47,160
I like it.

452
00:20:47,910 --> 00:20:50,110
It's not a holiday or anything.

453
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:52,220
Why did you come back all of a sudden?

454
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:54,840
I've got some business here.

455
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:56,960
What kind of business?

456
00:20:59,030 --> 00:20:59,680
Dad, Mom.

457
00:21:00,070 --> 00:21:00,830
Is our plant

458
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:02,550
not producing anymore?

459
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,400
It stopped producing long ago.

460
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,660
Many workshops have stopped operating.

461
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,200
Do you guys want to move to Shanghai
with me?

462
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:12,540
I'm not going.

463
00:21:12,570 --> 00:21:14,070
I wouldn't get used to it there.

464
00:21:14,070 --> 00:21:15,270
Everything would be unfamiliar.

465
00:21:15,270 --> 00:21:16,000
I'd be completely lost,

466
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,460
not knowing a single soul.

467
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:18,480
I'm not going.

468
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:19,510
Besides,

469
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,750
while I'm still in good health,

470
00:21:21,750 --> 00:21:23,000
I'm thinking of driving a taxi
for another couple of years

471
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,600
to save up some money for you.

472
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,160
This way, when you buy a house
in Shanghai in the future,

473
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,680
I'll cover the down payment for you.

474
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:29,240
Oh my.

475
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:31,650
Remember that.

476
00:21:31,650 --> 00:21:32,750
You have to remember that.

477
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:34,240
He's starting to talk big.

478
00:21:34,510 --> 00:21:37,690
The down payment in Shanghai
is pretty expensive, you know.

479
00:21:37,690 --> 00:21:39,730
Dad, about me buying a house,

480
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,560
you don't have to worry about it.

481
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:44,110
If you guys don't want to
go to Shanghai with me,

482
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:46,350
then I'll buy you a house
here in Tiecheng,

483
00:21:46,350 --> 00:21:46,790
alright?

484
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:47,270
Alright.

485
00:21:47,270 --> 00:21:48,070
Hearing you say that

486
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:49,310
is enough for us.

487
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:49,830
Yeah.

488
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:52,200
We're living really well here
at the East Chemical Plant.

489
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,660
The neighbors around us
are all old friends.

490
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,680
Don't worry about us. Seriously.

491
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:58,280
Yeah. We know everyone here.

492
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,410
We're used to it.

493
00:21:59,830 --> 00:22:02,270
It's just hard to leave your hometown,
you know.

494
00:22:02,270 --> 00:22:03,880
Your mom and I have talked it over.

495
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,960
We'll stay right here
at the East Chemical Plant

496
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,090
for our retirement.

497
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:09,160
Come on.

498
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,480
Son, have a drink.

499
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:16,690
Are we really not taking
that sewing machine?

500
00:22:16,830 --> 00:22:17,690
Yeah, leave it.

501
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:19,030
Let's take it.

502
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:21,440
Didn't our son say
he's got everything ready over there?

503
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:22,310
Don't take it.

504
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:24,750
-It's no trouble anyway...
-Mr. Gu.

505
00:22:25,340 --> 00:22:26,400
Are you moving now?

506
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:29,680
Yeah. Renovation on that house
has been finished for quite a while.

507
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,270
Our son has urged us to move
several times.

508
00:22:31,270 --> 00:22:31,750
Yeah.

509
00:22:33,070 --> 00:22:33,550
But...

510
00:22:33,750 --> 00:22:36,200
Why are you moving
in the middle of the night?

511
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,660
Xiaoman and the other kids

512
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,290
insisted on coming over to help me move.

513
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:41,720
I didn't want to hold up their work
during the day.

514
00:22:41,720 --> 00:22:42,650
But this is good.

515
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:46,070
This way, we can do it quietly
and not disturb the neighbors.

516
00:22:46,070 --> 00:22:46,830
It's okay.

517
00:22:47,510 --> 00:22:49,240
You're moving in with your son.

518
00:22:49,410 --> 00:22:50,410
It's a good thing.

519
00:22:50,830 --> 00:22:51,350
Right.

520
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:53,570
Come back and visit when you have time.

521
00:22:53,570 --> 00:22:54,570
Sure. We will.

522
00:22:55,790 --> 00:22:57,440
More and more people are moving away.

523
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:58,770
I was getting used to it,

524
00:22:59,030 --> 00:23:00,620
but now that Mr. Gu is moving too,

525
00:23:00,620 --> 00:23:01,820
I feel upset again.

526
00:23:05,110 --> 00:23:06,310
-Mr. Gu.
-All packed?

527
00:23:08,910 --> 00:23:09,990
I've taught for most of my life

528
00:23:09,990 --> 00:23:11,030
at our plant.

529
00:23:11,270 --> 00:23:14,550
And now, having you two cohorts of
students here to see me off—

530
00:23:14,550 --> 00:23:16,010
I'd say my teaching career

531
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:18,800
has come to
a perfect and fulfilling close.

532
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:19,690
Gosh.

533
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:21,000
You're not that old,

534
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,930
yet you talk like an old professor.

535
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:24,720
It's not like you're moving far away.

536
00:23:24,720 --> 00:23:25,480
It's only Tiecheng,

537
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:26,030
right?

538
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:27,920
Besides, the living conditions
and overall environment there

539
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:29,070
are better than here.

540
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:29,940
It's a good thing.

541
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:32,470
Yeah, we can go visit you
whenever we're free.

542
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:35,590
You guys—

543
00:23:36,510 --> 00:23:37,640
take care, alright?

544
00:23:37,790 --> 00:23:38,400
Okay.

545
00:23:39,110 --> 00:23:40,440
We will. Take care, alright?

546
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,550
Take care. Did you hear him?

547
00:23:41,550 --> 00:23:42,200
We will.

548
00:23:42,710 --> 00:23:44,640
I know you can't bear to
leave your students.

549
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:46,960
Didn't they say they'd come with you
to Tiecheng this time?

550
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:48,550
Why are you saying goodbye here?

551
00:23:48,550 --> 00:23:51,310
Right, right. We'll take a taxi
and head there first.

552
00:23:51,310 --> 00:23:53,110
You guys take a taxi
and start unpacking there.

553
00:23:53,110 --> 00:23:54,110
It might take us a bit longer.

554
00:23:54,110 --> 00:23:54,980
See you there then.

555
00:23:54,980 --> 00:23:55,830
Okay. Alright.

556
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:56,240
Alright.

557
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:56,550
Let's go.

558
00:23:56,550 --> 00:23:57,510
Put this on the truck.

559
00:23:57,510 --> 00:23:58,200
Put it on the truck.

560
00:23:58,200 --> 00:23:58,830
-Come on.
-You're driving?

561
00:23:58,830 --> 00:23:59,200
Give it to me.

562
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:00,260
Yeah, I'm driving.

563
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:06,640
Hello.

564
00:24:06,750 --> 00:24:07,160
Hello.

565
00:24:07,270 --> 00:24:08,510
I'm here to see Mr. Song.

566
00:24:08,510 --> 00:24:09,370
Register here.

567
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,440
Here, have some tea.

568
00:24:22,070 --> 00:24:24,640
It wasn't easy
to find our branch factory, was it?

569
00:24:24,640 --> 00:24:25,570
It was all right.

570
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:27,790
I used to live at East Chemical Plant.

571
00:24:27,790 --> 00:24:28,720
Though I've never actually been
inside here,

572
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:30,780
I know roughly where Factory No. 3 is.

573
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:35,040
So, Mr. Xia, you're
one of the factory kids?

574
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:35,720
Yes.

575
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,070
Look at you—young and promising,

576
00:24:38,070 --> 00:24:40,470
and thinking of giving back to
the factory.

577
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:42,240
Our East Chemical Plant
is being restructured,

578
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:44,820
and now foreign investors
also have a chance to acquire it.

579
00:24:44,820 --> 00:24:46,070
I've submitted your company's proposal

580
00:24:46,070 --> 00:24:47,590
to the PSAC.

581
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:50,980
On the whole, they approve of it.
But of course,

582
00:24:51,350 --> 00:24:54,200
if you could sweeten the terms a bit,

583
00:24:54,430 --> 00:24:57,160
it would make it much easier
to push this forward.

584
00:24:58,510 --> 00:24:59,570
I'm actually here this time

585
00:24:59,570 --> 00:25:01,400
to conduct an on-site inspection.

586
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:03,880
After all, investment can't be done
blindly.

587
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,010
Sure. I understand.

588
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,270
Mr. Xia.

589
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:09,740
Come on, let me show you around the plant.

590
00:25:10,030 --> 00:25:10,680
No need.

591
00:25:10,830 --> 00:25:12,640
I already had a look when I arrived.

592
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:13,440
You already had a look?

593
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,070
Yeah.

594
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,740
Where did you look?

595
00:25:16,310 --> 00:25:18,270
Mr. Song, this plant

596
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,500
been shut down for a while, right?

597
00:25:23,790 --> 00:25:24,480
Yes.

598
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:25,920
Well...

599
00:25:26,550 --> 00:25:28,270
As for this branch factory,

600
00:25:28,830 --> 00:25:31,290
we haven't had any orders
for almost 2 years.

601
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:33,880
The workers are all on standby at home.

602
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:34,940
But let me tell you,

603
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:38,530
we've maintained the machines very well.

604
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:42,210
As soon as we get orders,
we can start production right away.

605
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,470
Okay, I see.

606
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,150
I'll go back
and discuss it with the company.

607
00:25:49,150 --> 00:25:49,950
No problem.

608
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:51,790
Money doesn't grow on trees,

609
00:25:51,810 --> 00:25:52,380
right?

610
00:25:52,790 --> 00:25:53,160
Okay.

611
00:25:53,180 --> 00:25:54,240
I'll head back now.

612
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:57,440
Guys, since so many people
are moving away these days,

613
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:59,440
why don't we start a moving company?

614
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:01,890
That doesn't seem necessary.

615
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,360
Look.

616
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,350
With so many people moving away,

617
00:26:06,350 --> 00:26:08,550
they surely have bulky items at home.

618
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,900
They d-definitely need to find
a moving company and a truck.

619
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:11,830
They can't possibly do it themselves.

620
00:26:11,830 --> 00:26:13,400
We've got nothing better to do anyway.

621
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:15,070
We might as well make some money.

622
00:26:15,070 --> 00:26:15,880
Besides,

623
00:26:16,160 --> 00:26:19,440
we've known everyone in the factory
since we were kids.

624
00:26:19,790 --> 00:26:21,000
Consider it a send-off for them.

625
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:21,750
But here's the thing.

626
00:26:21,750 --> 00:26:23,640
With the wages we're getting now,

627
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,070
it's barely enough to cover food.

628
00:26:25,070 --> 00:26:26,270
Who would have the money to hire us?

629
00:26:26,270 --> 00:26:27,540
Aren't they all moving...

630
00:26:27,540 --> 00:26:29,540
Aren't they all moving to Tiecheng?

631
00:26:29,550 --> 00:26:31,200
Tiecheng's been developing quite well—

632
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:31,930
really well.

633
00:26:32,030 --> 00:26:35,200
Going forward, our real target is actually

634
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:36,920
t-t-the business and projects
over there in Tiecheng.

635
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,310
This is a major deal.

636
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:40,480
Just one of those moving company trucks

637
00:26:40,480 --> 00:26:42,160
would cost a fortune, wouldn't it?

638
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,270
We don't have to get a fancy truck.

639
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:45,110
And it doesn't have to be new.

640
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:46,480
Go find that—what's his name again—

641
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:49,080
Bin. Isn't he dealing in
second-hand cars now?

642
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:50,680
Ask him to get one for you.

643
00:26:51,240 --> 00:26:52,750
Well... Xiaoman, here's the thing.

644
00:26:52,750 --> 00:26:53,680
Getting a truck is no problem.

645
00:26:53,680 --> 00:26:54,270
It's just

646
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,440
I... I don't have money to pay him.

647
00:26:56,440 --> 00:26:57,200
To get a truck for us—

648
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:57,880
I don't have that money.

649
00:26:57,880 --> 00:26:58,920
I was only asking you to go find him...

650
00:26:58,920 --> 00:26:59,920
I was not asking you to...

651
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:00,880
Talking to you

652
00:27:00,900 --> 00:27:02,200
is really going to be the death of me
one day.

653
00:27:02,200 --> 00:27:04,400
If we can't afford to buy one,
renting works too.

654
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,440
In the next couple of days,

655
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:07,570
I'll discuss it with Da and the others.

656
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:10,550
Aren't there a lot of people moving
around here lately?

657
00:27:10,550 --> 00:27:12,270
I want to start a moving company
with them.

658
00:27:12,270 --> 00:27:13,030
What do you think?

659
00:27:13,030 --> 00:27:15,510
Sounds good. There should be
plenty of work recently.

660
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:16,550
Business should be good.

661
00:27:16,550 --> 00:27:18,480
Right, I saw that
a lot of people are moving.

662
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:20,520
And it just so happens that
Da and Dongdong are both home.

663
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:21,450
Why don't you...

664
00:27:21,550 --> 00:27:22,920
Why don't you open your moving company

665
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,580
upstairs from my flower shop?

666
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:27,200
This way, I can take orders for you
when you're busy,

667
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,270
like answering the phone,
things like that.

668
00:27:28,270 --> 00:27:29,070
What do you think?

669
00:27:29,070 --> 00:27:30,960
Sure. Since there'll be many people there,

670
00:27:30,960 --> 00:27:33,100
we can all help out
if your flower shop needs anything.

671
00:27:33,100 --> 00:27:33,830
Sounds good.

672
00:27:33,930 --> 00:27:35,060
We can also find a job

673
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:36,600
for Mr. Ding and the others.

674
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,110
Xia Lei.

675
00:27:39,380 --> 00:27:40,350
Long time no see, Chunchun.

676
00:27:40,350 --> 00:27:41,160
Long time no see.

677
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,360
What brings you back?

678
00:27:44,620 --> 00:27:45,210
Xia Lei,

679
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:45,900
look at you.

680
00:27:46,350 --> 00:27:48,400
Aren't you just the kind of person
they talked about when we were kids—

681
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:48,920
what's that called again—

682
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:50,550
a man of striking appearance,

683
00:27:50,550 --> 00:27:51,940
returning home in glory?

684
00:27:51,940 --> 00:27:53,470
What are you talking about?

685
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:55,200
It's not like that. I'm just used to it.

686
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:56,800
Why... Why did you come back?

687
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,030
I'm on a business trip.

688
00:27:58,030 --> 00:27:59,590
You call coming home a business trip?

689
00:27:59,590 --> 00:28:00,880
Well, I have work to do.

690
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,220
Alright, alright.

691
00:28:03,500 --> 00:28:05,230
Do you n-need me for something?

692
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:07,880
Are you two together?

693
00:28:09,590 --> 00:28:10,850
I-Isn't this obvious?

694
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:13,340
No, no. Well...

695
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:15,050
W-We're just getting to know each other.

696
00:28:15,050 --> 00:28:16,070
-Right?
-What are you talking about?

697
00:28:16,070 --> 00:28:17,200
You're right. We're together.

698
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:19,930
Hey, don't hold my hand
when you're holding hers.

699
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:22,310
I have to congratulate you then.

700
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:23,480
You've recovered,

701
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,670
and you've got a girlfriend.

702
00:28:24,670 --> 00:28:26,150
I wouldn't have recovered without her,

703
00:28:26,150 --> 00:28:26,630
right?

704
00:28:27,070 --> 00:28:29,000
By the way, I just thought of something.

705
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:31,000
What are your plans for the future?

706
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:33,040
We were just talking about that.

707
00:28:33,070 --> 00:28:35,200
Lots of people are moving around here.

708
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:38,110
And since Da and Dongdong are both home,

709
00:28:38,130 --> 00:28:40,510
I thought we could team up

710
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:41,790
to start a moving company

711
00:28:41,790 --> 00:28:42,920
and make some money.

712
00:28:43,190 --> 00:28:44,850
Moving is a booming business.

713
00:28:44,920 --> 00:28:46,680
And the living facilities here

714
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:47,750
can't keep up anymore.

715
00:28:47,750 --> 00:28:48,910
I should just kick you out.

716
00:28:48,910 --> 00:28:50,030
Is this not your home or something?

717
00:28:50,030 --> 00:28:50,790
Don't just stand here and talk.

718
00:28:50,790 --> 00:28:52,200
He just got back. Let's talk inside.

719
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:52,680
-I'll pour you some tea.
-Yeah, right.

720
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:53,510
-Let's go inside.
-Let's go.

721
00:28:53,510 --> 00:28:54,840
-Come on in.
-I'll pass.

722
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:56,590
It's almost dinner time.

723
00:28:56,590 --> 00:28:57,830
-I'll cook for you.
-I need to go home for dinner.

724
00:28:57,830 --> 00:28:58,830
Tomorrow,

725
00:28:58,830 --> 00:28:59,920
I'll call everyone

726
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:00,570
to have a meal together.

727
00:29:00,570 --> 00:29:01,270
-Okay?
-Okay.

728
00:29:01,270 --> 00:29:02,330
Give me a call then.

729
00:29:03,070 --> 00:29:03,680
Okay. Alright.

730
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:03,960
Go ahead.

731
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:04,400
I'll cook for you tomorrow.

732
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:04,680
You guys do your thing.

733
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:05,500
Okay. Bye-bye.

734
00:29:05,500 --> 00:29:06,030
Bye-bye.

735
00:29:07,270 --> 00:29:08,890
If you have time tomorrow morning,

736
00:29:08,890 --> 00:29:10,000
I'll take you to meet someone.

737
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:10,880
Who are we meeting?

738
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:11,880
We're meeting...

739
00:29:13,920 --> 00:29:14,750
Meeting...

740
00:29:15,790 --> 00:29:16,920
Someone important.

741
00:29:19,510 --> 00:29:20,160
It's here.

742
00:29:20,350 --> 00:29:20,920
Are they here?

743
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:21,920
No, not yet.

744
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,270
Slow down a bit.

745
00:29:23,270 --> 00:29:24,530
I keep hearing noises.

746
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:27,400
Hey, slow down a bit. I can't keep up.

747
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:28,180
Can't make it up?

748
00:29:28,180 --> 00:29:28,830
Move your legs faster.

749
00:29:28,830 --> 00:29:29,590
How do I look?

750
00:29:29,750 --> 00:29:30,480
Is my hair okay?

751
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:31,350
Yeah, your hair is fine.

752
00:29:31,350 --> 00:29:32,150
Do I look okay?

753
00:29:32,150 --> 00:29:33,400
-We're here.
-Where is it?

754
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:34,510
I should slick it down a bit.

755
00:29:34,510 --> 00:29:36,030
As if a calf licked it.

756
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:37,360
No.

757
00:29:37,380 --> 00:29:38,110
That's good.

758
00:29:38,830 --> 00:29:39,490
We're here.

759
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:40,690
Where is it?

760
00:29:40,720 --> 00:29:41,920
This room right here.

761
00:29:46,080 --> 00:29:48,010
Maybe you should go in by yourself.

762
00:29:48,180 --> 00:29:50,030
Why? We're already at the door.
Don't be shy.

763
00:29:50,030 --> 00:29:51,200
You've met my mentor before, right?

764
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:52,200
Well, it's true that I've met him,

765
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,330
but that was before.

766
00:29:53,350 --> 00:29:54,350
I didn't know back then

767
00:29:54,350 --> 00:29:55,790
what your relationship was.

768
00:29:55,790 --> 00:29:56,510
What do you think our relationship is?

769
00:29:56,510 --> 00:29:57,480
He's my mentor—

770
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:58,590
like a parent to me.

771
00:29:59,070 --> 00:29:59,550
Well...

772
00:30:00,030 --> 00:30:02,550
It's exactly because he's like a parent

773
00:30:02,580 --> 00:30:03,150
that...

774
00:30:06,970 --> 00:30:07,790
Well, isn't that exactly why we are here?

775
00:30:07,790 --> 00:30:09,490
To talk about something serious?

776
00:30:09,490 --> 00:30:11,420
You're even making me nervous now.

777
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,480
-Let's go.
-They've been waiting for so long...

778
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:14,270
I see them.

779
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:15,070
Mr. Ding!

780
00:30:15,070 --> 00:30:15,790
I see them.

781
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:16,550
Mrs. Ding!

782
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:18,920
Come on. Go welcome them.

783
00:30:20,680 --> 00:30:21,000
Mr. Ding.

784
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:21,730
You're here.

785
00:30:22,720 --> 00:30:23,720
This is Chunchun.

786
00:30:24,120 --> 00:30:24,760
Chunchun.

787
00:30:26,830 --> 00:30:27,480
We brought some fruit.

788
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:28,240
Here's some fruit.

789
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:28,720
Oh, this...

790
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:29,780
Alright, alright.

791
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:31,200
You're too polite, bringing fruit.

792
00:30:31,200 --> 00:30:31,920
Sit, sit.

793
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,310
Come on, sit down.

794
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:35,880
Auntie, let me help you.

795
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:36,640
No, no, no need to help.

796
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,310
Don't get your hands dirty.

797
00:30:37,310 --> 00:30:37,720
I insist.

798
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:38,240
Sit down, come on.

799
00:30:38,240 --> 00:30:39,680
-Sit down.
-I can't just stand by and watch.

800
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:40,200
-Be good.
-I'll…

801
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:41,440
I'll learn. I want to learn from you.

802
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,550
What's there to learn?

803
00:30:42,550 --> 00:30:43,960
I've never made these before.

804
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:44,960
Like this, right?

805
00:30:45,680 --> 00:30:46,200
I've never made these before.

806
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,730
This girl is pretty decent.

807
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:48,520
Like this?

808
00:30:48,540 --> 00:30:49,680
What's there to learn?

809
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:50,310
She's quite down-to-earth.

810
00:30:50,310 --> 00:30:51,270
Good. Yours looks good.

811
00:30:51,270 --> 00:30:51,720
Right, right.

812
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:52,720
Apply some flour.

813
00:30:52,790 --> 00:30:54,000
Honesty is what matters.

814
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:55,160
Yeah, just press it like this.

815
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:56,680
She's articulate,

816
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:57,680
knows respect,

817
00:30:57,680 --> 00:30:58,480
and is polite.

818
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:00,880
And she never complains when working.

819
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:01,810
Can do anything.

820
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,160
As long as you like her.

821
00:31:04,160 --> 00:31:05,700
Yeah, they all look the same.

822
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:06,270
Rolled round like the moon.

823
00:31:06,270 --> 00:31:07,130
D-Don't stir this yet.

824
00:31:07,130 --> 00:31:08,160
Stir it when we wrap them.

825
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:08,600
Okay.

826
00:31:10,270 --> 00:31:11,070
Hey,

827
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:13,720
w-why are you bundled up so tight?

828
00:31:13,720 --> 00:31:14,720
Hurry up and take it off.

829
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,750
Why are you dressed so formally
just to chop green onions?

830
00:31:16,750 --> 00:31:18,000
Give me a break.

831
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,170
You only bought this little meat,
and you want him to take off his clothes?

832
00:31:21,170 --> 00:31:21,790
God.

833
00:31:22,110 --> 00:31:23,680
That meat I bought... I mean...

834
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:25,740
Xiaoman, what were you saying earlier?

835
00:31:25,740 --> 00:31:26,220
What...

836
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,080
What company do you want to open?

837
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:29,030
A moving company.

838
00:31:29,030 --> 00:31:30,030
A moving company?

839
00:31:30,720 --> 00:31:33,920
Well, isn't everyone from our plant
moving out these days?

840
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,680
So I was thinking
we could get some people,

841
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:36,400
get a truck,

842
00:31:36,510 --> 00:31:38,950
and run the route
from Tiecheng to our plant.

843
00:31:38,950 --> 00:31:39,460
Okay.

844
00:31:40,350 --> 00:31:41,110
I support you.

845
00:31:41,110 --> 00:31:42,680
Young people should just go for it.

846
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:43,680
But you have to be careful.

847
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:45,200
This... Well...

848
00:31:46,160 --> 00:31:48,240
For long-term development, you know?

849
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:50,400
I know. It's fine for now.

850
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,350
The main issue right now is that

851
00:31:51,350 --> 00:31:53,350
I need someone to hold down the fort.

852
00:31:53,950 --> 00:31:55,810
Just go look for someone outside.

853
00:31:56,350 --> 00:31:57,790
It's hard to find this kind of person.

854
00:31:57,790 --> 00:31:59,270
You know what kind of person we need?

855
00:31:59,270 --> 00:32:02,200
Someone capable, experienced,
and respected.

856
00:32:02,350 --> 00:32:04,270
He has to be able to sit there
like a general.

857
00:32:04,270 --> 00:32:04,920
Only then can I work.

858
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:05,920
I went home and thought about it
for quite a while.

859
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:07,480
And then I thought, isn't that my mentor?

860
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:08,550
Isn't that you?

861
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:13,120
Xiaoman, I understand your intentions.

862
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:14,270
But I'm getting old.

863
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,520
I'd just be idling anywhere.

864
00:32:19,950 --> 00:32:21,840
Work requires the young and strong.

865
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:23,550
But what was that you just said?

866
00:32:23,550 --> 00:32:25,680
What kind... What kind of person
do you need to hold down the fort?

867
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:29,590
Capable, experienced, and respected.

868
00:32:31,030 --> 00:32:31,510
Right?

869
00:32:31,530 --> 00:32:33,070
Doesn't that sound a lot like you?

870
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:34,480
I'm not short on young, strong guys.

871
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:38,940
What I'm missing over there is someone
like you—a strategist, a top-tier brain.

872
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,860
I won't argue with you on that.

873
00:32:42,310 --> 00:32:43,510
Mom, is Dad back yet?

874
00:32:43,510 --> 00:32:44,480
No.

875
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:46,440
Why don't we stop waiting here

876
00:32:46,460 --> 00:32:47,680
and go look for him again?

877
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:48,330
But...

878
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:49,400
Where could he have gone?

879
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,400
-Let's go.
-Let's go look again.

880
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:51,070
This way, Chief Engineer Yan.

881
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:52,270
-Don't be anxious.
-You're almost home, right?

882
00:32:52,270 --> 00:32:52,880
Come on, go home.

883
00:32:52,880 --> 00:32:54,000
He's back.

884
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,500
Dad, where have you...

885
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:57,200
I went to the factory.

886
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,680
Where did you run off to?

887
00:32:58,880 --> 00:32:59,720
You didn't even tell us.

888
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,000
I was s-so worried.

889
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:01,720
Why should you be worried?

890
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:03,240
Could I get lost in the factory?

891
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,640
Look, I even ran into him.

892
00:33:04,850 --> 00:33:05,980
Just an inspection.

893
00:33:06,030 --> 00:33:07,070
We'll head back first.

894
00:33:07,070 --> 00:33:08,070
-Okay.
-Alright?

895
00:33:08,210 --> 00:33:09,830
Mom, take Dad upstairs first.

896
00:33:09,830 --> 00:33:11,680
Okay. You guys... You guys chat.

897
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:12,270
Let's go.

898
00:33:18,480 --> 00:33:19,550
Thank you.

899
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:20,580
It was nothing.

900
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:23,350
Chief Engineer Yan was...
I happened to be wandering around,

901
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:24,750
and I bumped into him.

902
00:33:24,750 --> 00:33:25,720
Chief Engineer Yan was inspecting
over there,

903
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:27,520
so I accompanied him for a while.

904
00:33:32,270 --> 00:33:34,160
My dad has Alzheimer's.

905
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:35,990
He probably thought...

906
00:33:36,210 --> 00:33:37,020
I... I know.

907
00:33:39,070 --> 00:33:41,070
When did you get out of the hospital?

908
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:45,270
I... I just got out recently.

909
00:33:46,830 --> 00:33:47,890
Are you recovered?

910
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,660
Well... This kind of thing...

911
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:52,030
I guess I-I'm recovered.

912
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:53,150
But with this kind of illness,

913
00:33:53,150 --> 00:33:55,420
you can't really say it's completely gone,
you know?

914
00:33:55,420 --> 00:33:57,490
But I-I can live a normal life now.

915
00:34:01,070 --> 00:34:01,880
Actually,

916
00:34:04,220 --> 00:34:06,680
I visited you once
when you were in hospital.

917
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:09,639
When was that?

918
00:34:09,800 --> 00:34:11,929
Just a while ago, when I just came back.

919
00:34:12,659 --> 00:34:14,260
I heard you were in hospital,

920
00:34:14,870 --> 00:34:16,270
so I went looking for you.

921
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:18,440
They said you were in the greenhouse.

922
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:22,110
I went there and saw you wiping that...

923
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:24,909
Glass jar?

924
00:34:25,070 --> 00:34:26,150
Right, right.

925
00:34:26,960 --> 00:34:28,480
You seemed to be doing well,

926
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:29,810
so I didn't disturb you.

927
00:34:30,550 --> 00:34:32,710
I was just finding something to do.

928
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:40,110
Now that you're back,

929
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,940
a-are you going abroad again?

930
00:34:46,469 --> 00:34:48,800
I brought some work back with me
this time.

931
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:50,170
My dad is sick, you know.

932
00:34:50,590 --> 00:34:51,550
I need to see

933
00:34:51,820 --> 00:34:53,590
how his condition develops

934
00:34:54,070 --> 00:34:56,400
before deciding when to return to France.

935
00:34:59,000 --> 00:34:59,880
France...

936
00:35:03,070 --> 00:35:04,280
Is France nice?

937
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:14,930
Pretty nice.

938
00:35:16,590 --> 00:35:18,480
That's good then. Glad to hear it.

939
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:23,240
I... Well... I should get going.

940
00:35:25,030 --> 00:35:26,280
Oh, right.

941
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,710
I'm meeting your dad tomorrow at 10 a.m.

942
00:35:28,710 --> 00:35:30,030
I'm taking him to see someone.

943
00:35:30,030 --> 00:35:31,110
Let your mom know.

944
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:32,190
Who are you seeing?

945
00:35:32,710 --> 00:35:33,670
Mr. Gu.

946
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:35,320
The one who caught Xia Lei and me
cheating?

947
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:36,050
Yeah, right.

948
00:35:36,070 --> 00:35:38,230
When I went to the hospital to see you,

949
00:35:38,230 --> 00:35:39,070
I saw him there too.

950
00:35:39,070 --> 00:35:40,330
Yeah, he was there too.

951
00:35:40,650 --> 00:35:43,380
Funny how we all ended up in the hospital.

952
00:35:45,490 --> 00:35:47,420
Why are you taking my dad to see him?

953
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:49,070
Mr. Gu is actually...

954
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,400
Pretty... Pretty mysterious these days.

955
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,530
Normal people can't make sense of him,

956
00:35:55,030 --> 00:35:56,590
but for some patients in the hospital,

957
00:35:56,590 --> 00:35:57,480
he talked them into recovery—

958
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:58,960
even talked them into discharge.

959
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:01,430
I thought Chief Engineer Yan
could chat with him.

960
00:36:01,430 --> 00:36:03,630
Maybe they'll just click or something.

961
00:36:04,940 --> 00:36:06,880
It doesn't matter if they don't click.

962
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:09,010
At least my dad will have someone
to talk to.

963
00:36:09,010 --> 00:36:10,010
That's good enough.

964
00:36:10,010 --> 00:36:11,470
Yeah, that's what I meant.

965
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:12,230
Thanks.

966
00:36:13,360 --> 00:36:14,130
Don't mention it.

967
00:36:14,130 --> 00:36:15,480
If your dad ever gets lost again,
just let me know.

968
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:17,810
I have a knack for
finding him at the plant.

969
00:36:18,190 --> 00:36:19,190
I'll be going now.

970
00:36:23,070 --> 00:36:23,880
Xiaoman.

971
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,590
Live well.

972
00:36:30,430 --> 00:36:31,180
You too.

973
00:36:49,320 --> 00:36:52,150
Mr. Gu, I'm back.

974
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:55,200
How have things been?

975
00:36:58,990 --> 00:36:59,590
It's okay.

976
00:37:00,590 --> 00:37:01,360
Mr. Gu.

977
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:03,490
This is Chief Engineer Yan.

978
00:37:04,030 --> 00:37:07,360
He's like an older brother to me.
He hasn't been well lately.

979
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,590
It's Alzheimer's.

980
00:37:10,150 --> 00:37:11,840
I think in this field,

981
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,660
you're a real expert.

982
00:37:14,700 --> 00:37:15,630
Curse him out a bit

983
00:37:15,630 --> 00:37:16,710
and wake him up.

984
00:37:19,190 --> 00:37:20,920
Once there's tap water on the moon,

985
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:23,920
it'll directly impact
Earth's auto industry.

986
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:25,280
When eating noodles,

987
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,110
we can't have any distracting thoughts.

988
00:37:27,110 --> 00:37:28,670
The amino acids produced by humans

989
00:37:28,670 --> 00:37:31,480
affect generations of small animals.

990
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:34,800
Human beings perceive this world

991
00:37:34,820 --> 00:37:36,770
-from within three-dimensional space.
-He's on. He's on.

992
00:37:36,770 --> 00:37:37,550
Listen to this.

993
00:37:37,550 --> 00:37:39,150
Many phenomena can't be explained,

994
00:37:39,150 --> 00:37:41,210
so they are attributed to illnesses.

995
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:44,670
Unable to distinguish between
past and present—

996
00:37:44,700 --> 00:37:47,030
from our quantum mechanics perspective,

997
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:49,070
this is quantum entanglement.

998
00:37:49,710 --> 00:37:51,280
The so-called quantum entanglement is when

999
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:52,110
two quanta

1000
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:54,800
break the limits of time and space

1001
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:56,460
and influence each other.

1002
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:59,800
One quantum is the past you,

1003
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:03,070
and the other is the present you.

1004
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:05,880
For the past you,

1005
00:38:06,150 --> 00:38:07,800
the future hasn't happened yet,

1006
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:10,510
but you'll have a vague sense of it.

1007
00:38:11,100 --> 00:38:12,910
It's called déjà vu.

1008
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:14,800
It's French.

1009
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:17,110
It means "already seen."

1010
00:38:18,180 --> 00:38:20,570
I think I understood that last part.

1011
00:38:21,150 --> 00:38:22,950
I... I think I have that feeling.

1012
00:38:23,550 --> 00:38:25,230
It's like the past me

1013
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:27,170
sometimes asks the present me,

1014
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:28,960
"did you do it right,

1015
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:30,220
or did you do it wrong?"

1016
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:34,070
So if, after calculation,

1017
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:36,320
I find that the past me

1018
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,590
did it wrong,

1019
00:38:38,900 --> 00:38:39,650
what then?

1020
00:38:40,550 --> 00:38:42,350
What is wrong? And what is right?

1021
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:44,410
Past and present are no different.

1022
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:46,320
No choice is wrong.

1023
00:38:47,110 --> 00:38:49,360
Everything in the present will vanish.

1024
00:38:51,130 --> 00:38:53,260
It's just a difference in the process.

1025
00:38:53,670 --> 00:38:54,280
How was it?

1026
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:55,550
It was an epiphany.

1027
00:38:55,590 --> 00:38:56,130
Right?

1028
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:57,280
It worked, huh?

1029
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:58,610
I'm fully enlightened.

1030
00:38:58,670 --> 00:38:59,280
That's great.

1031
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:01,670
Just like
"I couldn't see the true face of Mount Lu

1032
00:39:01,670 --> 00:39:03,630
because I was in the mountain myself."

1033
00:39:03,630 --> 00:39:04,450
Xiaoman. You're leaving?

1034
00:39:04,450 --> 00:39:06,150
Then we've come to the right place.

1035
00:39:06,150 --> 00:39:06,860
Makes sense, right?

1036
00:39:06,860 --> 00:39:07,460
Sure.

1037
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,010
Want more cucumber?

1038
00:39:22,190 --> 00:39:23,650
And a bit more carrot, too.

1039
00:39:25,670 --> 00:39:27,670
It reminds me of when I was little.

1040
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:33,760
My dad was always away from home,

1041
00:39:35,510 --> 00:39:37,370
and my mom cooked for me every day.

1042
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:53,400
Is something on your mind, Sweetie?

1043
00:39:56,840 --> 00:39:58,640
I went to Xiaoman's house today.

1044
00:39:59,510 --> 00:40:01,760
I wanted to thank him—

1045
00:40:02,670 --> 00:40:05,710
for taking Dad to see Mr. Gu,

1046
00:40:06,810 --> 00:40:08,440
and for taking care of Dad

1047
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,980
and finding someone to chat with him.

1048
00:40:12,670 --> 00:40:14,270
What else did you talk about?

1049
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:16,710
I

1050
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:18,920
saw...

1051
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:23,620
him and Chunchun together
through the window,

1052
00:40:24,710 --> 00:40:27,440
so I didn't go in.

1053
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:37,710
Actually, when I broke up with him
in France,

1054
00:40:40,630 --> 00:40:42,710
I knew that we

1055
00:40:43,590 --> 00:40:45,320
would never get back together.

1056
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:47,320
But today,

1057
00:40:48,670 --> 00:40:51,070
suddenly seeing him with a new girlfriend,

1058
00:40:55,230 --> 00:40:56,150
I still felt...

1059
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:00,190
A little bit...

1060
00:41:03,920 --> 00:41:08,550
Actually, seeing Xiaoman move on,

1061
00:41:10,630 --> 00:41:12,280
I'm quite happy for him.

1062
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:15,480
I'm also happy for you

1063
00:41:16,150 --> 00:41:18,070
that you think that way.

1064
00:41:25,030 --> 00:41:25,510
Mom.

1065
00:41:26,490 --> 00:41:29,240
You've never told me the story
between you and Dad.

1066
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:31,190
There's no story between us.

1067
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:35,020
Unlike you guys,
we didn't have so many stories.

1068
00:41:35,710 --> 00:41:38,030
Back when he first came to the plant,

1069
00:41:38,300 --> 00:41:41,560
you just followed him.
What were you thinking at that time?

1070
00:41:42,510 --> 00:41:44,630
My mind was very simple back then.

1071
00:41:43,140 --> 00:41:49,190
♪ Spin and spin, spin a few circles
back to the starting point ♪

1072
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,520
I just liked your dad.

1073
00:41:48,070 --> 00:41:50,550
Your grandma wouldn't let me leave home,

1074
00:41:49,790 --> 00:41:56,310
♪ Save and save, accumulate bitterness
to exchange for sweetness ♪

1075
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:52,920
but wherever your father went,

1076
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:54,110
I just followed him.

1077
00:41:56,990 --> 00:42:03,790
♪ When will we stand side by side again,
and when will we say goodbye? ♪

1078
00:42:04,730 --> 00:42:11,130
♪ Like the swaying swing ♪

1079
00:42:11,620 --> 00:42:15,400
♪ If seas turn to mulberry fields ♪

1080
00:42:15,450 --> 00:42:18,670
♪ Whether flat or winding ♪

1081
00:42:18,690 --> 00:42:22,520
♪ If rain wets your face ♪

1082
00:42:22,820 --> 00:42:28,830
♪ Chat at the old spot
after all storms have passed ♪

1083
00:42:29,700 --> 00:42:33,420
♪ Time train goes round and round ♪

1084
00:42:33,440 --> 00:42:36,680
♪ Day by day, year by year ♪

1085
00:42:37,220 --> 00:42:40,510
♪ Wave your hands and stride ahead ♪

1086
00:42:40,940 --> 00:42:44,180
♪ The years are kind ♪

1087
00:42:44,360 --> 00:42:47,820
♪ Migratory birds fly over
the mountain top ♪

1088
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:51,770
♪ Get through the coldest day ♪

1089
00:42:53,610 --> 00:42:56,410
♪ Wait till the kapok blooms ♪

1090
00:42:57,220 --> 00:43:00,300
♪ When you come rushing back still ♪

1091
00:43:01,390 --> 00:43:03,760
♪ The young you ♪
